To gauge the practical utility for such generated sensing platform within biological samples, this assay was validated for detecting MOR in urine samples. Consequently, prevalently available urine was spiked with MOR across a 1.25–22.5 μg/mL range, and the assay was conducted using the method elaborated in the aforementioned section. The innovative colorimetric approach was found to have a recovery of between 101.0% and 107.0% with an RSD value under 5% (Table 2
                        ). The outcomes show that even in the presence of a urine matrix, the devised assay performs as expected. Table 3
                         compares analytical results for differing MOR detection methods. The colorimetric biosensor fabricated in this study, thus, illustrates a viable new approach to presumptive testing for MOR.
